Taiwan Stock Movers: Advanced Semiconductor, Alpha Networks Inc.

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-08-16T05:48:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/taiwan-stocks-advanced-semiconductor-alpha-networks-htc.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 20.80 points, or 0.3 percent, to
7,798.59.  Advanced Semiconductor Engineering Inc. (2311)  (2311 TT), a chip
packing and testing company, rose 0.7 percent to NT$27.45, its
highest close since Aug. 2. The company plans to buy back up to
34 million common shares, or 0.56 percent of total outstanding
shares, it said in a statement. The company plans to buy back
shares at between NT$20 and NT$45 each from Aug. 16 to Oct. 15,
2011, it said.  Alpha Networks Inc. (3380)  (3380 TT), a networking equipment
maker, climbed 6.8 percent to NT$22.85, the highest close since
Aug. 4. The company plans to buy back 15 million common shares,
or 3.15 percent of total outstanding stock.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
